```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Tier3 [@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent (CLI)]
        CA[pi-coding-agent]
        CA_Deps[External Libs<br/>chalk, diff, extract-zip,<br/>glob, yaml, cli-highlight, ...]
    end

    subgraph Tier2 [@mariozechner/pi-agent-core (Agent Runtime)]
        AC[pi-agent-core]
    end

    subgraph Tier1 [@mariozechner/pi-ai (LLM Abstraction)]
        AI[pi-ai]
        AI_Ext[Provider SDKs<br/>@anthropic-ai/sdk, openai,<br/>@google/genai, @mistralai/mistralai,<br/>@aws-sdk/client-bedrock-runtime]
    end

    subgraph Support [Supporting Packages]
        TUI[pi-tui (Terminal UI)]
    end

    CA --> AC
    AC --> AI
    CA --> TUI

    AI --> AI_Ext

    style CA fill:#e1f5e1
    style AC fill:#e1f5e1
    style AI fill:#e1f5e1
    style TUI fill:#f5e1e1
    style AI_Ext fill:#f5f5e1

    classDef tier3 fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#388e3c,stroke-width:2px
    classDef tier2 fill:#c5cae9,stroke:#3f51b5,stroke-width:2px
    classDef tier1 fill:#ffccbc,stroke:#d84315,stroke-width:2px
    classDef support fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#fbc02d,stroke-width:2px

    class CA tier3
    class AC tier2
    class AI tier1
    class TUI support
```

---

**Explanation**:
- Direction: Top-down dependencies (Tier3 → Tier2 → Tier1).
- `pi-tui` is independent support package used by Tier3.
- Provider SDKs are external dependencies of Tier1 (`pi-ai`).
- No cyclic dependencies: Each tier only depends on lower tiers.
- `pi-coding-agent` also has many external utility libraries (chalk, diff, extract-zip, glob, yaml, ...) for CLI/application functionality.
